channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Family of explorer who died in Titan sub implosion seeks over $50M in lawsuit
item.description: The family of a French explorer known as “Mr. Titanic” who died in a submersible implosion has filed a wrongful death lawsuit seeking more than $50 million that accuses the sub’s operator of gross negligence

item.title: The secret behind Disney's streaming success: Disney CFO
Video shows dog starting fire after chewing on lithium-ion battery
item.description: Video footage from inside the home showed how a dog accidentally started a fire by biting on a portable battery until sparks flew out and flames grew.

item.title: 2 arrested for planning terror plot at Taylor Swift show in Vienna: Police
item.description: Security measures have been increased for Taylor Swift's concerts in Vienna, Austria, this week after two suspects were arrested for allegedly plotting a terror attack.

item.title: Row over Tory MP's Allahu Akbar arrest call

item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris announced Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz as her running mate Tuesday.

item.title: Jan. 6 rioter taken into custody after threatening posts targeting Barrett, Garland
item.description: A man awaiting trial for charges stemming from his alleged participation in the Jan. 6 riot at the U.S. Capitol is in custody for threatening statements he made.

Democrats unite around Harris, Walz 2024 campaign ticket
item.description: Moderate Democrat and progressive lawmakers are uniting to support Vice President Kamala Harris and her newly-announced running mate Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz. CBS News political correspondent Caitlin Huey-Burns has more.

item.title: 5-year-old boy with autism rescued from pond after escaping from home
item.description: A 5-year-old boy with autism was rescued from a Florida pond after he wandered away from his home Tuesday evening, authorities said.
